header.gameNote: SPORTSTIME OHIO BCA CLASSIC AT COLUMBUS OH

article.headline: Princeton 56, Alabama A&M 39
article.story: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Kyle Koncz scored 19 points and Princeton built a big lead with its withering defense to beat Alabama A&M 56-39 on Sunday to take fifth place in the BCA Classic at Ohio State's Value City Arena. Koncz hit 4-of-8 3-pointers -- matching A&M's total in 16 attempts -- and made all seven of his free throws. Justin Conway added 11 points for the Tigers (2-1). Cornelius Hester and Evan Hilton each had 11 points for the Bulldogs (1-2). The Tigers built a 32-15 halftime lead by limiting A&M to 30 percent shooting from the field (6 of 20). Koncz was 4-of-6 behind the arc and had 15 points in the opening half. With Princeton ahead 17-13 and 5 minutes left in the half, Koncz was fouled while shooting a 3 and made all three free throws to start a 15-2 run until the break. He later added a 3-pointer in the surge. The lead never dropped below 13 points in the second half.
